  "one_liner": "Inside an untrained generator hides a subnetwork that matches the dense model — found by moment-matching scores.",
  "tldr": "Strong lottery tickets ask whether a random network already contains a working subnetwork, no weight updates allowed. We bring this to generators: only a binary mask is learned over an untrained model, guided by moment-matching scores (MMD). With 10% of weights left, it matches the dense baseline."
